	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">psycopathicteen wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I always wondered how developers knew exactly how much memory/PPU bandwidth they needed to reserve.</div>
<br />I don't think they always did... I think that the first time you work with a platform it's hard to know where the limits are, but after several projects on the same platform you start to guess much better! =)
<br />
<br />I know that when I am designing my programs I have several backup plans, in case my primary plan turns out to be impossible to implement. So for each different part of my programs I think of 2 or 3 ways they could be implemented, and when placing all the parts together I decide how to distribute my resources, possibly using the simpler/faster/smaller solutions in some cases.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


